==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: catalyze
<hw>catalyze</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr>
<fld>(chemistry)</fld> <def>to cause (a chemical reaction) to proceed
more quickly by contacting the reactant(s) with another substance;
<as>as, moisture <ex>catalyzes</ex> the oxidation of iron in
air</as>.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled <asp>catalyse</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> change by catalysis, cause to catalyze.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

